<br>
Here's a fact: evocation helps with Breath of Ro. Which is  oftentimes unsung as an awesome group spell, because of a paticular side effect it has.<br>
<br>
It CANCELS Mob damage shields. Yep, burns them away. Before I get the &quot;duh, I knew that&quot; flames, I have grouped with 3 druids in the past week WHO DID NOT KNOW THAT. So this is for those like them.<br>
<br>
It costs 250 mana, and still fizzles. But with spec. evo, it fizzles/costs less. So, you can help protect your hasted tanks by not only lowering mob AC/fire resist and doing 950 points of damage, but by removing mob damage shield as well.<br>
<br>
An advantage to using Ro over dispelling magic? Well, dispell can dispell ANYTHING- DOTS, shaman slows, snare, root, debuffs, whatever. Breath of Ro merely removes damage shield. So you don't have to worry about reapplying all those spells if they get stripped.<br>
<br>
So there's some group value to specializing in evocation, other than nuking :)<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=archidamus>Archidamus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#333399>(3/22/01 2:04:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2261.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A good reason to spec. in Evocation</span><hr size=1> Awesome!  I am level 51 and did not know that.  Does it remove all damage shields including the thorn types or does it only remove fire-based damage shields? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urpthehotrod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RpTheHotrod</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#333399>(3/22/01 6:48:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2261.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Not to mention...</span><hr size=1> Quad kiting is ALOT easier... less mana :D <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unortherner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Northerner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 113<br> <font color=#333399>(3/23/01 4:48:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2261.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Not to mention...</span><hr size=1> I had never heard this either... lets not talk too much about this though or someone might change it hey?  Does it work on all damage shields though or just the Mage/Wizard line? (fire based)  It cancels thorns and the Necro one (Banshee) as well?  There might be interesting uses for this perhaps.  Hehe, now I just need four levels to test it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubuteaoregalis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ButeaoRegalis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#333399>(3/23/01 12:31:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2261.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A good reason to spec. in Evocation</span><hr size=1> I know that Dreth addressed specialization properly, but I just wanted to point something out to those new to specialization and that may have misread his post:<br>
<br>
Specialization helps reduce the mana cost of a spell. It has nothing to do with fizzles. Dreth was correctly pointing out that your fizzles will cost less, not that specialization reduces fizzles in any way.<br>
<br>
Just thought I'd clear that up for any lurkers. :-)<br>
<br>
Buteao<br>
Level 51 Druid on Xegony <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udreth1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dreth1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 129<br> <font color=#333399>(3/23/01 12:38:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2261.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A good reason to spec. in Evocation</span><hr size=1> It removes any/all damage shields. Wizard O'Keils line, Mage lava line, druid/ranger thorn line.<br>
<br>
A warning though- as always, be wary when dotting during multiple pulls. Let the enchanter mez the other targets  and tanks lock on a target before you go stripping dam shield. Remember- dots break mez :)<br>
