 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscirocco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scirocco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2978<br> <font color=#333399>(3/23/01 12:42:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2261.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A good reason to spec. in Evocation</span><hr size=1> Um, Butaeo?  Specialization DOES reduce fizzle rates.  The fizzle rate quickly reaches the floor of 5%, however, so this benefit of specialization quickly disappears. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujadaepacifica.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jadae Pacifica</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/pacificjade/bunclover.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 287<br> <font color=#333399>(3/23/01 5:32:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2261.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A good reason to spec. in Evocation</span><hr size=1> Alteration, forever :) Breath of Ro is a waste of a spell slot even if your evocation- the spell is bugged anyhow. High taunt, poor damage ratio for mana spent, high resist. Go through your book or a spell sheet-check out how many are alteration. Better yet, try to channel ensnare while being mauled-Ya an alteration spell ;) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=crescent>Crescent</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#333399>(3/26/01 11:41:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2261.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.kc.rr.com/hideaway/images/compass.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Fizzles yes..  channel? no</span><hr size=1> Specialization does reduce the fizzle rate of spells cast.  It also reduces the mana used when that spell is cast if a successful check against your spec skill is made.<br>
<br>
It does nothing for channeling ability when casting spells though. <p><img src=http://home.kc.rr.com/hideaway/images/crescent.gif></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscirocco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scirocco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3004<br> <font color=#333399>(3/26/01 2:55:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2261.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fizzles yes..  channel? no</span><hr size=1> Agreed, it doesn't help channelling or interruptions.<br>
<br>
I have seen the &quot;mana reduction on successful check&quot; claim before, but I have seen no evidence of it in the game.  I did a sample of 25 casts of the same evoc. spell with maxxed specialization in evoc., and EVERY CAST the mana savings was approx. 15%.  So either the mana reduction is per cast, or the chance of failing the mana reduction check at maxxed specialization is so small as to not be noticeable (and thus we can go ahead and treat it as mana reduction per cast). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujadaepacifica.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jadae Pacifica</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/pacificjade/bunclover.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 296<br> <font color=#333399>(3/26/01 5:21:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2261.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fizzles yes..  channel? no</span><hr size=1> Its arguable and not proven. I have been inclined to say it does from channeling anything from lvl 29 ensnare to lvl 60 Nature's Touch multiple, multiple times with severe battle scars. I highly doubt I could do that with Wildfire. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugadzoook.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gadzoook</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 94<br> <font color=#333399>(3/27/01 6:30:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2261.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Channeling..</span><hr size=1> Personally, I've always attributed it to some spells being more robust than others.  I'm spec alt and channel heals (sup, chloroblast etc) just fine yet Wildfire you have to breathe on me the wrong way to interrupt me.  Yet, I don't attribute it to specialization as I tend to channel other spells like winged death and ES arms very easily as well while root is something that I channel with mediocrity.<br>
<br>
-Gadz <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubuteaoregalis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ButeaoRegalis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#333399>(3/27/01 12:27:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2261.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fizzles yes.. channel? no</span><hr size=1> Damn... I'm clearly wrong. :-) There I go spouting something that I &quot;heard&quot; 20 levels ago. Thanks all for the corrections.<br>
<br>
Buteao <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umilodruid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Milodruid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333399>(3/27/01 5:52:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2261.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fizzles yes.. channel? no</span><hr size=1> I specialized in Evocation a long time ago.  Specialization DOES NOT AFFECT FIZZLES!!!!  It only affects the amount of mana used.  Thats all, thats it PERIOD.  I always thought that if you/group has more damage output,mob dies faster=less healing=more exp.  Just the way I see it.<br>
