<br>
Milolas is right on the money. When will people stop believe the things disproven ages ago. Specialization will have a chance for lowering the mana cost after the spell has begun to cast. That is it. And what this means is if you want to cast starfire for example. You need 250 mana to cast this. If you have under 250 mana you will not be able to cast this. However when you have 250 mana or more you can cast this, and then before the spell goes off it will be decided whether it will cost the full 250 mana or some reduced amount. <br>
<br>
And the biggest reason to go Specialize in Evoc instead of alteration is because our alteration spells are already much more efficient then our evoc spells. <br>
