<br>
I'm definitely agreeing with Talanos. Druids simply aren't healers. The regeneration line of spells help offset this, but we don't have the heals to keep a main tank in peak condition during combat. Plus, with the new Heal Aggro tweaks, we certainly don't have the AC to handle getting pounded at the higher levels.<br>
<br>
Support for this can also be found with the original Kunark line of spells. Druids are given enhanced regeneration and blasting spells nearly on par with mages, yet only Superior Heal at level 53. Obviously Verant didn't intend for us to supplant Clerics. This may have shifted with the introduction of Chloroblast and Nature's Touch. But, even with this help, we'll always be backup healers for the reasons I mentioned above.<br>
<br>
Further support comes from the ratios:<br>
<B>Alteration</B><br>
Greater Healing = 2.00<br>
Superior Healing = 2.33<br>
Chloroblast = 2.44<br>
Nature's Touch = 2.44<br>
<br>
<B>Evocation</B><br>
Starfire/Ice = 2.44<br>
Scoriae = 2.75<br>
Exile Summoned = 2.90<br>
Frost = 3.05<br>
Wildfire = 3.20<br>
<br>
Our best healing <B>never</B> matches our ability to blast. The only caveat to my analysis is levels 30 thru 48. At these levels, our abillity to blast and heal is roughly equal -- only to be offset by the Regen line and the Swarm line.<br>
<br>
Unlike most other classes, we can gain XP solo nearly as effectively as we can grouped. When soloing, I find myself using Evocation far more than Alteration. One Ensnare typically last the whole combat and I usually use Grasping Roots (35mana) since root is most often resisted. The rest is all Conjuration and Evocation -- <B>especially</B> while Quading!<br>
<br>
Regardless of all this blathering, I find myself blasting more than healing. Look at the way you play and make the choice that makes sense to you! You can always change it later by going to the Temple of Solusek Ro. <br>
<br>
{Find Ostrom and give him a ruby (~170pp) and he'll reset all your specialisations to 49. (He asks for 50gp afterwards, but you don't have to give it to him) Immediately and repeatedly cast the lowest level type of spell you want to specialise in on yourself until you hit 50. Don't port first since that <B>might</B> pop Alteration to 50!}<br>
<br>
